column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/192722e8c1075ec834fc0b04e5cba8e9dc5d2265 for binaries and test log.\nThis test script verifies pulls every time they are updated. It, however, dies sometimes and fails to test properly.  If you are waiting on a test, please check timestamps to verify that the test.log is moving at http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/cu
I'm working on a pull request that removes the CENT-related rule.\n
Closing this given the code is to be replaced anyway. Thanks for feedback everyone.\n

It's safe to say that all code will be eventually replaced.

It depends on the time frame whether it makes sense to merge this or not. In general I'm very much in favor of pulls that improve documentation in the code.
I'm inferring that's an imminent PR, but obviously very happy to re-open if not!\n
